review_blob:
12 OZ. BOTTLE. BIG HOP BITTERNESS.
WELL BALANCED. COULD NOT TELL IT WAS 8.8%ABV. AS ALL SAM ADAM BEERS--- THERE IS PLENTY OF HOP (ASTRINGENT) BITTERNESS THAT MUST BE FROM A HARD WATER PROFILE. I WOULD BUY THIS ONE AGAIN.

NICE POUR. GOOD CARBONATION.
NICE STRONG  AND SOUR GREEN APPLE AROMA AND TASTE.
THIS BEER CAME IN A SAMPLER 8 PACK FOR 16 BUCKS. STICKER SHOCK, BUT WORTH IT.

THIS IS A NICE WHIT. NOT OVERLY SPICEY OR CLOVEY. IT POURED MILKEY WHITE WITH PLENTY OF CO2.
THIS BEER WENT DOWN EASY LEAVING ME WANTING ANOTHER.TOO BAD. IT CAME IN A SAMPLER PACK WITH OTHER GREAT BREWS.

DFH MAKES SOME GREAT BEERS.
I MUST HAVE GOTTEN AN OLD BOTTLE.
THE APRICOT AROMA AND TASTE WERE ABSENT. SO WHATS LEFT? AN IPA BY DFH. I WAS LET DOWN AGAIN.

THIS IS A BIG BIG BEER. BEAUTIFUL COLOR AND HEAD.
THIS BEER COMES ON STRONG BUT FINISHES NICELY.
JUST GOT 12 OZ BOTTLES. NOT THE SAME AS PICTURED. MAY BE NEW LABEL. MAYBE I JUST DONT REMBER. ILL HAVE ANOTHER.

GET A WHIFF OF HOPS.
THIS BEER FILLS YOU NOSE WITH HAPPINESS.
LINGERING HEAD WITH LASTING LACING. BURSTING WITH FLAVOR AND BITTERNESS. GREAT BALANCE.
ITS WORTH THE PRICE.

AROMA WAS SLIGHTLY GRASSY.
THE APPEARANCE WAS DARK FOR A PALE ALE. THE FLAVOR WAS ....SO SO.TERRY WOULD NOT GET THIS AGAIN
beer_name: Two Brothers Heavy Handed India Pale Ale
